				<li id="16628278" class="cmnt-root" data="6" data-d="1650283572000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578562/Serpentbone-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">18 Apr 2022 08:06</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16628278" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This is the most strange weapon of the game, cant use ashes of war, but it needs 25+ upgrades, has a unique R2 and apply deadly poison.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16628278" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16628278" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>6</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16628278"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16628278" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16628278"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16626722" class="cmnt-root" data="11" data-d="1650261410000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578562/Serpentbone-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">18 Apr 2022 01:56</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16626722" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Tried this out in invasions and fight clubs at RL 30.<br/><br/>The Serpentbone Blade uses most of the standard Uchigatana moveset, but its R2 attacks are replaced with a side-ways double slash (Can be followed up by another R2 double-slash). First hit of the double slash deals significantly less damage than the second, but if you hit the first attack you&apos;ll probably hit the second too. Running R2 is still the same roll-catching thrust of the Uchigatana, which is a big plus. The weapon art is a series of quick strikes much like the R2, and is divided into three parts, where the final attack is a delayed overhead slash that deals a good amount of damage.<br/><br/>The weapon deals poison damage but notably has no Arcane scaling, does not cause bleed, cannot be buffed with grease, and it cannot be infused, so you&apos;re stuck with the Dex. scaling as is. The poison however is twice as powerful as standard poison (15 damage per tick as opposed to 8 damage from a poison pot, tested on the Stormhill trolls.). The duration is much shorter than standard poison, which works in your favor if you use the Kindred of Rot&apos;s Exultation talisman, as the shorter duration makes re-application of the poison in a fight more plausible. <br/><br/>So far I&apos;ve been having a lot of fun with the weapon. The lack of bleed probably makes it inferior to the other katanas (Though you can&apos;t roll the poison proc. in PVP.), but I&apos;ve seen a good amount of success at these lower levels. I can&apos;t imagine it scales better than the other weapons in its class, but it deals respectable damage with almost no stat investment into dex (17 dex plus 5 dex from the Soreseal.), which lets me put almost all points into vigor (27 vigor + 5 vigor from the soreseal.), so I&apos;m fairly tanky for this stage of the game (And I could optimize the build more, I have a few superfluous points in Strength.). The R2 is very nice and can be tapped for a double swipe which aggressive opponents tend to get caught by, and it has a pretty generous cone-shaped hitbox. It probably falls off in the lategame but in the early game it&apos;s a lot of fun and is surprisingly effective. Pick it up while you grab the Recusant&apos;s Finger in Volcano Manor.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16626722" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16626722" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>11</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16626722"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16626722" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16626722"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
